   CCR Trainees Assembly

   The CCR Trainees Assembly is composed of non-tenured and non-tenure
   track M.D.s, Ph.D.s, or equivalents and predoctoral intramural
   scientists organized to foster the professional advancement of its
   member clinicians and scientists at CCR. The Trainees Assembly
   organizes and promotes educational activities such as training courses
   and seminars, identifies potential employment opportunities in both
   traditional and non-traditional career paths, assists in the
   orientation of new trainees, and provides an atmosphere of
   intercommunication among members. The assembly is working to enhance
   the intramural training program, foster communication among fellows and
   the CCR community, and serve as a liaison to administration programs
   affecting the trainingexperience.

